%% ML training pipeline (Mermaid)
flowchart TB
    RAW[data/raw.parquet<br/>pulled from ES by 01_ingest.py]
    RAW --> FE[02_features.py<br/>feature engineering]
    FE -->|numeric features| NUM[20 numeric cols<br/>lengths, ratios, signature flags, time]
    FE -->|categorical features| CAT[4 cat cols<br/>service, protocol, method, country]
    FE -->|scale| SCALER[StandardScaler<br/>saved as scaler.joblib]
    FE -->|one-hot| OHE[pd.get_dummies<br/>column list saved as feature_columns.json]
    NUM --> COMB[features.parquet]
    CAT --> OHE
    OHE --> COMB
    SCALER --> COMB
    COMB --> SPLIT[Stratified 80/20 split]
    SPLIT -->|train| CV[5-fold stratified CV]
    SPLIT -->|test| HOLD[test set held out]
    CV --> MODELS{6 models}
    MODELS --> M1[LogisticRegression]
    MODELS --> M2[DecisionTree]
    MODELS --> M3[RandomForest]
    MODELS --> M4[SVC rbf]
    MODELS --> M5[XGBoost]
    MODELS --> M6[LightGBM]
    M1 & M2 & M3 & M4 & M5 & M6 -->|refit on train| REFIT[trained model]
    REFIT -->|predict test| EVAL[04_evaluate.py]
    HOLD --> EVAL
    EVAL --> CM[confusion_matrix_*.png]
    EVAL --> ROC[roc_curve_*.png per best]
    EVAL --> SUM[summary.json + model_comparison.csv]
    EVAL -->|best by F1 macro| TM[trained_models/<br/>best_model_*.joblib<br/>+ scaler + feature_columns + labels]
